enter

public void enter(Tree tree,
                  Entry entry)
           throws SELMA.SymbolTableException
Enters an id together with an entry into this SymbolTable using the current scope level. The entry's level is set to currentLevel().

Throws:
SELMA.SymbolTableException - when there is no valid current scope level, or when the id is already declared on the current level.

retrieve

public Entry retrieve(Tree tree)
                               throws SELMA.SymbolTableException
Get the Entry corresponding with id whose level is the highest. In other words, the method returns the Entry that is defined last.

Returns:
Entry of this id on the highest level null if this SymbolTable does not contain id
Throws:
SELMA.SymbolTableException
